# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHAT IS .gitignore AND WHY IS IT USED?
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The .gitignore file tells Git which files and folders should NOT be tracked
# or uploaded to the repository.
#
# Not every file inside a project should be stored in GitHub:
# - Automatically generated files
# - System files (like macOS .DS_Store)
# - Python cache folders
# - Virtual environment folders
# - IDE/editor configuration files
# - Secret or environment files
#
# Ignoring these files keeps the repository clean, secure, and lightweight.
# Below are the ignore rules specifically chosen for this Python Tkinter project.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python cache files
# These are automatically generated by Python and should not be committed.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Virtual environment folders
# These folders can be very large and are recreated on each machine.
# They should never be included in a Git repository.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.venv/
venv/
env/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE/editor configuration files
# These files contain personal settings and are not part of the project itself.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS system files
# macOS automatically creates .DS_Store files; they are irrelevant to the project.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Log files
# Used for debugging, not needed in the repository.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment or secret files
# These may contain API keys or private settings and MUST NOT be shared publicly.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.env

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build and distribution folders
# Although not used in this assignment, these are common Python outputs.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
build/
dist/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Temporary files
# Sometimes created by GUI libraries like Tkinter.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ignore all PNG files except the one used in README.
# Only 'rize.png' (the screenshot for documentation) should be included.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.png
!rize.png

